Comment: I hate this movie. It angers me¬†that they took a book with a serious message‚Ä¶and added so much silly filler to it. I am not saying that I don‚Äôt think movies should have fun in them ‚Äì Dr Seuss stories are full of fun‚Ä¶but he would not be happy to know that this movie contains obnoxious kid humor. Neither would he be happy about the hypocrisy (if you don't know what I mean it is this movie and its marketing betraying the original book's message). Dr. Seuss books do not¬†translate well into feature films because you have to add so much to fill out the story. I hated the Grinch movie, because the changes/filler added nothing to the story. The Horton Hears a Who movie had too many pop culture references (Like the anime reference...what was the point of that?) and the less said about the horrendous and inappropriate Cat in the Hat movie, the better‚Ä¶and now this one.¬†I understand the allure of creating a Seuss-like world on film. ¬†They should have just made¬†a movie version of the musical ‚ÄúSeussical.‚Äù At least it is the right length and they would not have to pad it with filler.
